Bao Viet Holdings Targets Pretax Profit to Rise 15% in 2011

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-30T06:34:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/bao-viet-holdings-targets-pretax-profit-to-rise-15-in-2011-1-.html
Bao Viet Holdings,  Vietnam ’s
biggest insurer, is targeting pretax profit to rise 15 percent
to 1.45 trillion dong ($69.4 million) this year, Hoang Viet Ha,
director of the company’s corporate secretarial division, said.  Bao Viet expects consolidated revenue to rise 15 percent to
14.8 trillion dong and total assets to increase 27 percent to 57
trillion dong, Ha said at a conference in Hanoi today.  The company had an audited consolidated pretax profit of
1.255 trillion dong and consolidated revenue of 12.86 trillion
dong last year, Ha said.  Shares of Hanoi-based Bao Viet rose 3.5 percent to 75,000
dong at the 11 a.m. local-time close on the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange. The company gained 16 percent this year, while
the benchmark VN Index dropped 5.1 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 oha3@bloomberg.net  